c regime incorporated elements from both the Old Regime and French Revolutionary military culture to craft a new military culture, characterized by loyalty to both Napoleon and the preservation of French hegemony in Europe. Underscoring this new, hybrid military culture were five sources of motivation: honor, patriotism, a martial and virile masculinity, devotion to Napoleon, and coercion. Forging Napoleon's Grande Armée vividly illustrates how this many-pronged culture gave Napoleon’s soldiers reasons to fight.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aMasculinityzFrancexHistoryy19th century. 0aMilitary moralezFrancexHistoryy19th century. 0aNapoleonic Wars, 1800-1815. 0aSociology, MilitaryzFrancexHistoryy19th century. 0aSoldiersxAttitudeszFrancexHistoryy19th century. 0aSoldierszFrancexAttitudesxHistoryy19th century. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNew York University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z97831107064440 cprintz978081473748440uhttps://doi.org/10.18574/nyu/9780814737484.001.000140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780814708279423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780814708279/original  a978-3-11-070644-4  New York University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles